(dpa/NAN) A trainer airplane crashed at an airport in Indonesiaâ€™s Central Java province on Tuesday, killing its pilot, according to media reports. The pilot lost control of the Super Decathlon plane and crashed into a hangar during an aerobatic flight at Tunggul Wulung airport in Cilacap district, airport official Denny Ariyanto told the state-run Antara news agency. The pilot, an Indonesian Air Force member who served as a flight instructor at the Ganesha flight school, died on the scene, according to the report.